05/01/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police in the eastern province of Van have seized 120kg of heroin and 170kg of hashish, the Anadolu news agency reported on Monday (January 4th).
The drugs were hidden in rice sacks that were being transported from Iran to Istanbul.
Six people were arrested in the operation.
(Xinhua, Anadolu news agency - 04/01/10)
